Fortium] Leonardus de Portis (c. 1464 — 15 Sept. 1545), a lawyer of Vicenza, author of De sestertio, pecu- niis, ponderibus et mensuris antiquis, In his Suetonius, Aug. 1516, f0. ῑ, Egna- tius states that it had been composed five years before ; but the preface he wrote for an edition, perhaps the first, of the De sestertio, aa. et l., shows that it was not printed till some years after the Suetonius. This edition was re- printed by John Froben, aa. ; and by

Episcopius, March 1530. Panzer cites an edition, Rome, F. M. Calvus, 1524. Budaeus on reading Egnatius' note feared that he might be thought to have borrowed from Portius, and urged Egnatius to get the book printed (ΒΕ.4 24: 27 Nov. 1518). Erasmus raised the question of plagiarism again in 1527 (Lond. xx. 9, LB. 875), and moved Budaeus to inquire of J. Lascaris, who replied (ΒΕ.3 1·“. 131 νο) that he had seen a ms. copy of Portius’ book in Leo x's early years at Rome; cf. also BE.¹ 163, and Lond. xxiv. 18, LB. 1198. For Portius see A. G. di Santa Maria. Scrittori Vicentim', iii. (1775) pp. 210-28.
